# ERP Combobox Standard — Never Use `<Select>` with Async Options

## The Bug This Prevents

Shadcn/Radix `<Select>` resolves its display text (`SelectValue`) from `SelectItem` children
**at the time those items are mounted**. If options arrive asynchronously (any `useQuery`,
server action, or prefetch), and the items haven't mounted yet when the `value` prop is set,
Radix falls back to rendering the raw `value` string — the numeric database ID (`"1"`, `"2"`, etc.)
— instead of the human-readable label.

This was fixed in **ERP BASE 002F.5A.3X** (2026-06-14), where 11 `<Select>` fields across
5 Party Master files were converted to `ERPCombobox`.

## The Rule

> **Any field whose options come from a database, server action, `useQuery`, or any async source
> MUST use `ERPCombobox` (or an `ERPCombobox`-backed wrapper). Never use bare `<Select>` + `<SelectItem>`.**

`ERPCombobox` derives `selectedOption` via `.find()` on the live `options` array on every
render, so it always resolves the correct label as soon as options become available — with no
dependency on mount order.

## Approved Components (all backed by ERPCombobox internally)

| Use case | Component |
|----------|-----------|
| Generic async lookup | `<ERPCombobox value={...} onValueChange={...} options={[...]} />` |
| Party selection | `<PartySelect />` — `src/components/erp/party-select.tsx` |
| Country | `<CountrySelect />` |
| Emirate (cascades on countryId) | `<EmirateSelect countryId={...} />` |
| City (cascades on emirateId) | `<CitySelect emirateId={...} />` |
| Area/Zone (cascades on cityId) | `<AreaZoneSelect cityId={...} />` |
| Currency | `<CurrencySelect />` |
| Payment Term | `<PaymentTermSelect />` |
| Tax Type | `<TaxTypeSelect />` |
| Bank | `<BankSelect />` |
| Any ERP lookup category | `<LookupSelect category="..." />` |

All live in `src/components/erp/`.

## Correct Pattern

```tsx
import { ERPCombobox } from "@/components/erp/combobox";

// options built from async useQuery data
<ERPCombobox
  value={form.nature_id}                  // number | null — stored DB value
  onValueChange={(v) =>
    setForm((f) => ({ ...f, nature_id: v !== null ? Number(v) : null }))
  }
  options={(natures ?? []).map((n) => ({
    value: n.id,    // number — DB primary key
    label: n.name_en,  // string — human-readable display label
  }))}
  placeholder="Select nature..."
  required                                // use allowClear for optional fields
/>
```

## Forbidden Pattern

```tsx
// ❌ NEVER DO THIS with async options
import { Select, SelectContent, SelectItem, SelectTrigger, SelectValue } from "@/components/ui/select";

<Select value={natureId ? String(natureId) : ""} onValueChange={(v) => setNatureId(v ? parseInt(v) : null)}>
  <SelectTrigger><SelectValue placeholder="Select..." /></SelectTrigger>
  <SelectContent>
    {natures.map((n) => (
      <SelectItem key={n.id} value={String(n.id)}>{n.name_en}</SelectItem>
    ))}
  </SelectContent>
</Select>
```

## When `<Select>` IS Acceptable

Bare shadcn `<Select>` is only acceptable for **static, hardcoded options** that are always
present at render time — for example:

```tsx
// ✅ OK — options are static constants, never async
<Select value={alignment} onValueChange={setAlignment}>
  <SelectContent>
    <SelectItem value="left">Left</SelectItem>
    <SelectItem value="center">Center</SelectItem>
    <SelectItem value="right">Right</SelectItem>
  </SelectContent>
</Select>
```

## ERPCombobox Option Shape

```ts
interface ERPComboboxOption {
  value: string | number;  // stored DB value (ID)
  label: string;           // human-readable display name
  labelAr?: string;        // optional Arabic label
  code?: string;           // optional short code (shown when showCode=true)
  description?: string;    // optional search/filter text
  badge?: string;          // optional badge alongside label
  disabled?: boolean;
  raw?: unknown;           // original DB row for custom renderOption
}
```

## Key Props

| Prop | Purpose |
|------|---------|
| `value` | Current value (number \| string \| null) — the DB ID |
| `onValueChange` | Callback receives `string \| number \| null` — convert to number if needed |
| `options` | Array of `ERPComboboxOption` |
| `required` | Hides the clear button; deselect is blocked |
| `allowClear` | Shows ✕ button for optional fields |
| `showCode` | Prefixes label with `code - ` in the trigger |
| `loading` | Shows spinner while async data loads |
| `maxVisibleOptions` | Truncates long lists with a "type to search" hint |
| `disabled` / `readOnly` | Standard read-only states |
